Podosphere is a term used to describe the collective [[podcasting]] [[social network]] or [[community]]. Most likely derived from the term [[blogosphere]], used to decribe [[blogs]], it seems to have been first coined by Steve Gillmor, a podcaster, during the opening session on podcasting of the [[Bloggercon]] III conference.
While not nearly as popular as the term blogosphere, there are nealy 120,000 references to the word, according to a [[Google]] search.